  The main factors we're considering are....</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The main factors we're considering are the ability to take damage, deal damage, and the additional abilities of each class. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
I'm not sure how far we can be at this, but lets give it a shot. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Take Damage</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Rank:<br>
<br>
Warriors - Paladins - Shadowknights - Monks - Rangers - Rogues<br>
<br>
Reasoning:<br>
<br>
AC/Armor is not an issue.  It's not noticably harder to put together a 1200+ hybrid than it is to dress a warrior.<br>
<br>
While monks get the avoidance bonuses, hybrids get self buffs and heals to help them take damage, and are plate classes.<br>
<br>
Rogues just shouldn't be getting hit.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Deal Damage</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Rogues - Monks - Rangers - Shadowknights - Paladin/Warrior toss up<br>
<br>
Paladins are kings of the dink dink dink.<br>
<br>
Warriors tend to be forced to give up nice weapons for agroing weapons.  The common exception being the Windblade, which hybrids get to use too.<br>
<br>
Rogues are the far and away kings of sustained damage, rivaled only by the Mages.  Monks fall in at third there, with the wizards burst damage and the AAXP Rangers bringing up the rest of the pack.  The tank classes weren't invited to the race.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Additional Abilities</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Shadowknights - Paladins - Rangers - Rogues - Monks - Warriors<br>
<br>
Rogues:  Cuisonarts, additional abilities include the ability to slice, dice and juilienne fries.  Hide/Sneak.  Ability to reduce their own agro.<br>
<br>
Shadowknights: Amazing agro control powers.  DOTs, debuffs, AND the voice line.  Small pet ability.  Feign Death.<br>
<br>
Paladins: Amazing agro control powers, through stuns and heals.  Eventually the ability to rez.  Good buff lines.<br>
<br>
Warriors: Defensive.  AoE taunt through AA. Same 'skills' as other tanks for agro (Taunt, Kick, Beg). /shield  All other skills relate directly to either Taking or dealing damage.  Mostly taking.<br>
<br>
Rangers: Situational amazing DPS through extensive AA costs. Tracking.  Buffing.  Healing.  Agro control and agro removal spells.<br>
<br>
Monks: Feign Death.  High avoidance.  Do not require weapons.<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
How is my assessment?<br>
<br>
