<br>
Not only that, but as many have noticed, Warrior's are not even close to the aggro abilities of the Knight classes and in fact have some trouble getting groups because of this, since with the advent of Planes of Power that have yardtrash MOBs hitting for 300+ groups cannot afford to have the MOB anywhere else but at their Main Tank.<br>
The Main Tank NEEDS to hold that aggro, or they die.<br>
<br>
<br>
For Warriors it basically all boils down to a few things here :<br>
<br>
-Lacking in the equipment advantage department.<br>
-Lacking in the aggro department.<br>
<br>
<br>
First one would be more Warrior Only items, since All/All items becomes hideously expensive when they are tradable, which means the Warriors have trouble getting at them since they are lousy at making money.<br>
<br>
I mean hell, a Paladin / Shadowknight can go to the Bazaar and pick up a Shissar Knight Sword for about 100-200 pp ... that's a Dam 10 Delay 22 sword !<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Aggro ... I'd like to see a new ability at level 45 that enhanches the Taunt button. Taunt works just like before but have the ability to add another  &quot;tick&quot; of taunt at level 45 and then 1 more tick per 5 levels.<br>
<br>
 2 ticks at Level 45<br>
 3 ticks at Level 50<br>
 4 ticks at Level 55<br>
 5 ticks at Level 60<br>
 6 ticks at Level 65<br>
<br>
Every &quot;tick&quot; would work just like if you pushed a Taunt button, ie. it should be able to fail. And it would improve as your skill in it raises. Skill Cap at 250.<br>
<br>
That would most probably put Warriors back in the Main Tank seat, without them having to sacrifice too much in the weapon department.<br>
<br>
That way they would again live up to at least 2 of the 3 statements in the Manual description :<br>
<br>
